ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely recommend even to people not interested in IO since the techniques are becoming so ubiquitous in economics.
If you like empirical IO, then it should be your first choice.
I would recommend this lecture. The course is very well organized to learn all the tools and results of industrial organization from related theories to profound econometric methods.
The class covers both theoretical and empirical contributions in the IO literature. It gets you up to speed on the current state of the art and helps you develop analytical skills to evaluate papers.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It increased my understanding of empirical studies and related econometric methods.
The course gave me some key insight for the current work I am doing on auctions.
